President Donald J. Trump has issued a proclamation declaring November 2019 as National American History and Founders Month. In the proclamation, he emphasizes the importance of understanding and appreciating America's history and the principles on which the nation was founded. He highlights the sacrifices made by men and women throughout history to defend these principles and promote liberty and justice. The proclamation also calls for the development of a well-informed electorate and encourages citizens to reflect on the defining tenets that unite Americans. President Trump urges people to honor those who have contributed to the country's story and preserve their legacy for future generations. The proclamation calls for appropriate ceremonies and activities to observe National American History and Founders Month.